18/07/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- British Ambassador to Bulgaria Jeremy Hill, whose country currently presides over the EU, said on Monday (18 July) that the new Bulgarian government should be formed as soon as possible and continue with reforms.
Talking to local TV, Hill said that the EU had noted the will to further implement reforms, as demonstrated by party leaders in the new legislature.
Meanwhile, the high council of the Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP), which led after the 25 June parliamentary elections, has unanimously approved the candidacy of BSP leader Sergey Stanishev for prime minister.
He is expected to receive the mandate for forming a new cabinet from President Georgi Parvanov Monday afternoon.
(Nova TV, Dnevnik - 18/07/05)
